title: The Romance of Chinese Art (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
The Romance of Chinese Art
Garden City Publishing | 1936 | English | 288 pages | PDF | 36.4 MB

The material in this book is presented through the courtesy of the publishers of the Encyclopaedia Britannica. The text is composed of a selection of articles from its pages, and to its editors we are indebted<also for the use of the many colour plates and other illustrations. Warren E. Cox, Art Director of the Encyclopaedia Britannica, in his Preface explains the make-up and comments upon the scope and authority of this volume. We believe it to be the most compact and comprehensive reference book on the various branches of Chinese Art ever made generally available to students and laymen
